messages.message: Disparity between Build edits & Build results popping up again on the same document

Hey Will, this is a known issue with this release. We are actively fixing this. The workaround is to switch to use complex prompts.
https://aihub.instabase.com/docs/aihub/releasenotes/known-issues/index.html
Ah ok, good to know this is already flagged. This is using a complex prompt though
hmm the second field you mean? employee name?
yeah this is the prompt I'm using. have tried a few different iterations

I will have the team look into this asap. The known issue we discover is related to some differences in how we sent basic prompts in the pipeline from the build app vs in Refiner (some changes making build app getting better results than the generated app). But we did not find the case to exist in complex prompt. Is this a consistent behavior to all your files here? (all paystub files failed to get employer name? or just that particular file?)

thank you!! helpful context, I've heard batching prompts vs. sending individually effects results.

Only fails on 2 of 11 paystubs, which are both from States (only obvious pattern I see). Got all the others perfectly which is great. Attaching the other one below
Just for reference - when I ran this through last week it got it using a simple prompt
DM you for a few more debugging details for us :slightly_smiling_face:
Just an update, we got this to work; on the other side Eng has some digging to do. Thanks Will!
